import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['fertility'] = pd.to_numeric(data['fertility'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['fertility'])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['fertility'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility rates across different countries?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['life_expect'] = pd.to_datetime(data['life_expect'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['life_expect'], bins=20)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.bar(data['country'], data['fertility'], width=0.4, color='b', align='center', label='Fertility')
    ax.bar(data['country'], data['p_fertility'], width=0.4, color='g', align='center', label='Projected Fertility')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('How does the projected fertility rate compare to the actual fertility rate in different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
